I did not find a use for scissors for high scores, especially not on hard items as advised by a previous player.

Frame last, as combining framed items breaks the frame. Scissors can be used on soft items for moderate value, but the soft/hard + frame combo is more consistent for 50 points.

Always frame last, as framing an already framed item breaks it. Avoid overcomplicating combinations, and don't cut wood or hard items with scissors.

Avoid cutting hard items. If you cut artificial soft items (like paper/newspaper), they become 25 points, and framing them yields 45 points, which is a good alternative if you don't have the ideal soft/hard combination for 50. Always frame last, and don't overcomplicate combinations once you reach a high value.

message: The most reliable strategy for a 50-point score is to combine one soft ingredient with one hard ingredient, and then immediately frame the resulting blend. Always frame last, and do not combine already framed items. Cutting soft items (like ribbon or thread) usually gives 25 points, and framing the cut item can lead to 45 points, but the soft+hard+frame is generally better. Avoid cutting hard items as this can ruin them. Don't overcomplicate by adding too many components or using multiple tools on the same item, as this often reduces the value. Aim for simple, targeted combinations.
